context_meta.summary: “Our Cartoon President,” Showtime's animated comedy that skewers Donald Trump's White House, is hoping to shake up the 2018 Emmys … bigly. Best Animated Program has seen its fair share of repeat winners over the years, with 10-time champ “The Simpsons” being the granddaddy of all. “South Park” is next at three wins, followed by “Bob's Burgers,” “Futurama” and “Star Wars: Clone Wars” with two apiece. But “Our Cartoon President” has a secret weapon that could help it break through with Emmy voters: co-creator Stephen Colbert. Three coaches — Alicia Keys, Kelly Clarkson and Blake Shelton — turned their chairs around for Livia, and she ultimately chose to be on Team Alicia.
